@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Storage Workload Management - LUN Rebalance
' Section   : 14.12 Storage Workload Management Architecture
' Type      : Sequence diagram
' Message   : The storage capacity system uses LUN migration
'             to redistribute LUNs from over-utilized to
'             under-utilized cloud storage devices,
'             transparently to cloud consumers.
' ============================================================

!include ../../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

title 14.12 Storage Workload Management\nLUN Migration Sequence

skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

participant "Storage Capacity\nMonitor" as SCM
participant "Storage Capacity\nSystem" as SCS
participant "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
participant "LUN Migration" as LM
database "Storage 1\n(over-utilized)" as S1
database "Storage 2" as S2
database "Storage 3" as S3

== Configure ==
SCS -> SCM : 1. configure thresholds\n(workload and capacity)
SCM -> S1 : survey realtime
SCM -> S2 : survey realtime
SCM -> S3 : survey realtime

== Detect ==
SCM -> SCM : 2. workload on Storage 1\nreaches threshold
SCM -> SCS : 3. Storage 1 over-utilized
SCS -> SCS : 4. identify LUNs\nto move from Storage 1

== Rebalance ==
SCS -> LM : 5. migrate selected LUNs
LM -> S1 : extract LUNs
LM -> S2 : 6. place LUNs
LM -> S3 : 6. place LUNs
ASL -> ASL : watch and respond\nto fluctuations

== Power management ==
SCS -> S1 : keep in power-saving mode\nwhen access is light\nor only at specific times

note over LM
  LUN migration moves LUNs between
  storage devices without interruption
  and remains transparent to cloud consumers.
end note

note over SCS
  Mechanisms: cloud storage device, audit monitor,
  automated scaling listener, cloud usage monitor,
  load balancer, logical network perimeter.
end note

@enduml
